  <h2>The manifestation team determined that my child's behavior was:</h2>
  <p>not a manifestation of his or her  disability and the behavior involved <span class="def" id="drugs">drugs or alcohol.*</span> </p>
</div>
  <h2>Response: </h2>
<p>Whether  the school district decides to expel, suspend for more than five school days, alternative  educational services must be provided to the same extent that students without  disabilities are provided educational services. </p>
<p class="tip">Tip: Although your child  may be suspended or expelled, you may wish to ask the Section 504 team to develop  a <span class="def" id="bip">Behavioral Intervention Plan (BIP)*</span> that includes services and modifications  to address the behavior violation so that it is less likely to happen again  when he or she returns to school. You also may wish to request that your child  be evaluated for special education services.</p>
